        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>3d January 1866</date>.</p>
            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I send you the conclusion<lb/> of the Biography, and must ask your
                kind<lb/> attention to the additions to the last<lb/> copy sent which I hope will be
                in<lb/> time. One is an addition to the list of books,<lb/> the second is to come in
                as a note. I <lb/> have written them on a <sic>seperate</sic> sheet,<lb/> finding
                too that the Biography has swelled<lb/> to larger proportions than I at first
                thought.<lb/> I closed it with a few words words of dedication.<lb/> I think however
                they had better not<lb/> appear in the occident, but on a <sic>seperate</sic><lb/>
                page following the title—now the title to be<lb/> finished yet, I would say at the
                back<lb/> of that; but I presume that cannot be<lb/> easily done, &amp; the
                difference of expense<lb/> must be very trifling, so the <sic>seperate</sic> page
                is</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>perhaps the best. Please let me know<lb/> whether you have altered the grave
                error<lb/> to which I referred in my last and<lb/> which necessitates cancel pages.
                And<lb/> as you have all the copy now, I would<lb/> like to learn from you at
                your<lb/> earliest possible convenience what<lb/> I am to pay for the “Extras”.
                Further<lb/> as I have an idea of putting the<lb/> pamphlet in colored paper
                wrappers<lb/> with title, please let me know what<lb/> this will cost extra ere I
                decide—<lb/> of course I mean the difference between<lb/> receiving the work <hi
                    rend="underline">in sheets</hi>, and<lb/> sewed in pamphlet form &amp; covers
                    <add>?</add><lb/> as mentioned.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is not because the<lb/> pamphlet is <hi rend="underline"
                    >large</hi> that I have written<lb/> a dedication to <persName>Sir
                    Moses</persName> but<lb/> he has been like a second</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>parent to our family, and apart<lb/> from what he has done for
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/> and his many other claims to esteem<lb/> I
                always think of him, as I owe him<lb/> the highest gratitude. He was also<lb/> one
                of the best friends of my grandfather<lb/>
                <persName>Haham<add>?</add> Meldola's</persName>. When he goes, who<lb/> is there to
                have his place among the<lb/> orthodoxy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sam Benjamin</persName>
                <add>?</add> of this city<lb/> has lost his only son a fine young<lb/> man at
                    <placeName>Nassau</placeName>— <persName>Wm Benjamin</persName><lb/> is going in
                a few weeks to <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> on business and I will then
                ask<lb/> him to speak about your accounts.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am still owing you a<lb/> small balance which I will send<lb/>
                with the amount for the pamphlet<lb/> Please make a bill for it, adding<lb/> the
                sermon extras.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am not in receipt of the <date>Jany</date><lb/>
                <sic>occident</sic> yet. We seldom get it before<lb/> the middle of the month. Why
                is this?<lb/> I thought you published on the first?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should the note on <add>?</add><lb/> be not in time for the last
                copy sent<lb/> please add it to the copy now sent.<lb/> Its place would be at the
                beginning<lb/> of the copy thus “with the above list <add>Hebrew</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I must close, as I have to see<lb/> a gentleman or contemplate
                application<lb/> to our legislature for an Education<lb/> bill versus the Catholics
                — Please let<lb/> me hear from you soon.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I remain yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I have marked<lb/> the dedication D that<lb/> it may not be mixed with<lb/> the other
                copy. - When all is printed I<lb/> shall have a few errata to send you.</p>
        </body>
